OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FEngland and Scotland's group games at
OL,8,Fthe 2026 Fifa World Cup could kick off
OL,9,Fa national electricity spike
OL,10,Fequivalent to the total amount needed
OL,11,Fto power Leeds and Glasgow, according
OL,12,Fto Britain's energy system operator.
OL,14,FEnergy suppliers are preparing for
OL,15,Fpeaks of electricity demand as swathes
OL,16,Fof people across the UK settle in at
OL,17,Fhome or head to venues to watch the
OL,18,Ftournament.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FAnalysis by the National Energy System
OL,8,FOperator (Neso) predicts that each of
OL,9,FEngland and Scotland's games in the
OL,10,Fgroup stages could see national
OL,11,Felectricity usage increase by 600
OL,12,Fmegawatts.
OL,14,FThat is the equivalent of the total
OL,15,Felectricity demand for the cities of
OL,16,FLeeds and Glasgow combined.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FThe spike is set to come from people
OL,8,Fusing their TVs and devices to tune in
OL,9,Fto the matches, while demand is also
OL,10,Fforecast to rise at half-time and full-
OL,11,Ftime from actions such as opening the
OL,12,Ffridge or putting the kettle on.
OL,14,FFurthermore, Scotland's games are
OL,15,Fscheduled for late at night ` with the
OL,16,Ffirst kicking off at 2am UK time `
OL,17,Fmeaning they fall at times when
OL,18,Felectricity usage typically drops as
OL,19,Fpeople are sleeping.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FDespite increased usage, more energy-
OL,8,Fefficient TVs and devices mean Britain
OL,9,Fcould use around 20% less electricity
OL,10,Fto watch matches than in 1998 when
OL,11,FScotland last played in a World Cup.
OL,13,FThis is despite the population growing
OL,14,Fby around 11 million in that time.
OL,16,FHowever, total electricity usage could
OL,17,Fsoar by 18 gigawatts, or 60%, across
OL,18,Fthe 39 days of the World Cup, compared
OL,19,Fwith the last tournament in 2022,
OL,20,Faccording to the analysis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FThis year's tournament is larger than
OL,8,Fusual with a scheduled 104 games
OL,9,Fplayed by 48 teams, spread across more
OL,10,Fthan five weeks and in stadiums in the
OL,11,FUS, Canada and Mexico.
OL,13,FCraig Dyke, director of system
OL,14,Foperations for Neso, said this year's
OL,15,FWorld Cup "has more games than ever
OL,16,Fbefore, meaning we're likely to see a
OL,17,Fsurge in electricity demand across the
OL,18,Flonger tournament".
OL,26,@wD@KOUzD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780740351
OL,3,CElectricity usage forecast to spike
OL,4,Cduring England and Scotland World Cup
OL,5,Cgames
OL,7,FHe added: "While what happens on the
OL,8,Fpitch can always throw up surprises,
OL,9,Fwatching this year's World Cup will
OL,10,Falmost certainly be powered by the
OL,11,Fcleanest electricity in history."
OL,13,FMr Dyke said engineers will be
OL,14,F"working around the clock to balance
OL,15,Fsupply and demand" using energy
OL,16,Fforecasting and technologies such as
OL,17,Fbatteries and pumped hydro storage,
OL,18,Fwhich uses excess electricity during
OL,19,Foff-peak hours.
OL,26,@oD@KOUsD@aO]vD@AOUwD@RO]
